==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stipendiary
<hw>Sti*pen"di*a*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>stipendiarius</ets>: cf. F. <ets>stipendiaire</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Receiving wages, or salary; performing services for a stated price
or compensation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His great <qex>stipendiary</qex> prelates came with troops of
evil-appointed horseman not half full.</q>
<rj><qau>Knolles.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stipendiary</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Stipendiary
<hw>Sti*pen"di*a*ry</hw>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Stipendiaries</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <def>One who receives a
stipend.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If thou art become⟦br⟧
A tyrant's vile <qex>stipendiary</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Glover.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stipendiate</ent>⟦br⟧
